entry.def: The annulment of a contract or marriage is an official declaration that it is invalid, so that legally it is considered never to have existed.

example.ex: He may appeal to the Pope for an annulment of his 24-year marriage.
example.tran: 他可能会请求主教宣告他那长达24年的婚姻无效。

means.word_mean: 1. the state of being cancelled or annulled
2. (law) a formal termination (of a relationship or a judicial proceeding etc)
3. the act of abrogating; an official or legal cancellation
